lead_paragraph: A federal judge on Friday threw out an Obama administration decision to remove gray wolves in the western Great Lakes region from the endangered species list — a decision that will ban further wolf hunting and trapping in three states.

headline.main: Some Gray Wolves to Be Returned to Endangered List
headline.print_headline: Some Gray Wolves to Be Returned to Endangered List
